          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px;">
           <p style=3D"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 30px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0;">Welcome back to Dry Powder.=
 I=E2=80=99m <b>Bill Cohan</b>.<br/><br/>Earlier today, <b>Marc Rowan </b>b=
oarded a flight from Hong Kong to meet <b>Donald Trump </b>at Mar-a-Lago an=
d to discuss his possible appointment as the nation=E2=80=99s next treasury=
 secretary. I=E2=80=99m told the job is his to lose. <br/><br/>Indeed, if T=
rump chooses the universally respected and indisputably qualified Apollo C.=
E.O., it would certainly be the most <i>rational </i>decision Trump has mad=
e since descending the escalator in June 2015. But would Marc actually leav=
e his gilded perch to join this administration? (I have my thoughts, as I=
=E2=80=99m just finishing up a book on Apollo.) More on that, below the fol=
d. <br/><br/><i>But first=E2=80=A6</i><br/><br/></p><ul style=3D"margin:0;c=
olor:#000000;font-size:16px;line-height:30px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;l=
ist-style-type:square;mso-special-format:bullet"><li><i>Dylan on Joe &amp; =
Mika=E2=80=99s Mar-a-Lago adventure</i>: On Monday morning, MSNBC=E2=80=99s=
 connubial co-hosts <b>Joe Scarborough </b>and <b>Mika Brzezinski</b> infor=
med their loyal audience of almost a million viewers that they had recently=
 ventured south from their home in Jupiter to Mar-a-Lago. There, for the fi=
rst time in seven years, they met with <b>Donald Trump</b>=E2=80=94the very=
 man they=E2=80=99d spent the last <i>several years </i>vociferously pillor=
ying. Reading from their respective teleprompters with well-choreographed s=
olemnity, the couple conveyed this relatively benign news as though they we=
re disclosing their involvement in a top-secret nuclear negotiation. Or, as=
 CNN=E2=80=99s <b>John Berman </b>cheekily put it over on the rival network=
, =E2=80=9Cas if it were the Yalta summit.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Anticipating s=
ome blowback from their mostly liberal
coalition, Joe and Mika cast the Trump meeting as an attempt to foster a co=
nstructive dialogue. =E2=80=9CFor those asking why we would go speak to the=
 president-elect during such fraught times, especially between us, I guess =
I would ask back, =E2=80=98Why wouldn=E2=80=99t we?=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D Mika =
said. =E2=80=9CJoe and I realized it=E2=80=99s time to do something differe=
nt, and that starts with not only talking about Donald Trump, but also talk=
ing <i>with</i> him.=E2=80=9D Later, Mika also alluded to her father, <b>Zb=
igniew</b> <b>Brzezinski</b>, a top U.S. diplomat who served as <b>Jimmy Ca=
rter</b>=E2=80=99s national security advisor. She explained that maintainin=
g an open dialogue was =E2=80=9Ca task shared by reporters and commentators=
 alike.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>In light of Joe and Mika=E2=80=99s relatively exa=
lted status in the legacy media firmament, the disclosure became a minor so=
urce of fascination or frustration among their peers at 30 Rock, as well as=
 fodder for the media=E2=80=99s broader introspective post-election soul-se=
arching journey.
At MSNBC, weekend host <b>Katie Phang </b>wrote that =E2=80=9Cnormalizing T=
rump is a bad idea. Period,=E2=80=9D while <b>Stephanie Ruhle </b>sought to=
 convince her viewers that engagement was sound journalistic practice, and =
by no means a capitulation. Joe and Mika=E2=80=99s pilgrimage earned write-=
ups from the <i>Times</i>, the <i>Journal</i>, CNN, and so forth. It also i=
nduced predictable hysterics from the chronically outraged gasbag class, in=
cluding <b>Keith Olbermann </b>and <b>Megyn Kelly</b>. Meanwhile, the <i>Mo=
rning Joe </i>audience, already at a post-election nadir, dropped 17 percen=
t in the hour after Joe and Mika revealed their Trump meeting. The followin=
g day, the show=E2=80=99s ratings were down <i>38 percent</i> from this yea=
r=E2=80=99s average.<br/><br/>Alas, the debate over statecraft vs. surrende=
r diverted attention from the <i>real</i> palace intrigue. After all, Joe a=
nd Mika=E2=80=99s paeans to diplomacy belied the true motivation for their =
visit to Mar-a-Lago. In fact, the couple made the
trek to Palm Beach because they feared retribution, a fact that has thus fa=
r only been alluded to by CNN=E2=80=99s <b>Brian Stelter</b>. This week, so=
urces with direct knowledge of Joe and Mika=E2=80=99s thinking provided me =
with more details on those fears that, in addition to underscoring the bats=
hit-crazy nature of this moment in American politics, also offer insight in=
to the potential chilling effect that Trump=E2=80=99s return to the Oval Of=
fice might have on the news media writ large, and especially MSNBC. =E2=80=
=94<i>Dylan Byers</i> [<u><a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF=
9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUVEsxY2VOS3Z4R0VEWjdaRmdJcz0iLCJocmVmIjoia=
