          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><b>Marc Rowan</b> i=
s almost certainly too normal to be <b>Donald Trump</b>=E2=80=99s treasury =
secretary, especially in a cabinet composed mostly of quasi-lunatics withou=
t any qualifications for their jobs. Nevertheless, I=E2=80=99m told that Ma=
rc is flying back from Hong Kong to meet Trump at Mar-a-Lago today, and tha=
t the position is his to lose. In fact, assuming the two men get along, an =
announcement could be imminent. As everyone on Wall Street knows, you don=
=E2=80=99t get many chances to be treasury secretary. If chosen and confirm=
ed, Rowan would be the wealthiest treasury secretary ever=E2=80=94even weal=
thier than his new boss.<br/><br/>Rowan, of course, already has a big-time =
job as the C.E.O. of Apollo Global Management, running a business with some=
 5,000 employees, around $700 billion of assets under management, and a mar=
ket value of nearly $100 billion=E2=80=94up
nearly 250 percent since he took over from<b> Leon Black</b> in 2021. With =
all the funds that Apollo controls and that Rowan has a partnership stake i=
n, he will have a difficult time unwinding himself from the company. <b>Joh=
n Paulson</b>, another once-possible pick for treasury secretary, took hims=
elf out of contention after concluding that it would be too complicated to =
untangle himself from his hedge fund, or so we=E2=80=99re told. I=E2=80=99v=
e got to believe Marc would have an even harder time. <br/><br/>But I can=
=E2=80=99t think of a smarter, more qualified candidate, and he=E2=80=99ll =
probably take the job if Trump offers it. Black, who remains Apollo=E2=80=
=99s largest individual shareholder by far, agrees. He told me in a stateme=
nt: =E2=80=9CPresident Trump is a great businessman and the most financiall=
y savvy president of my lifetime. As with his first term, I=E2=80=99m confi=
dent he will successfully pick someone who is very talented and smart. I=E2=
=80=99ve known Marc Rowan for more than 40 years, and he is
exceptionally bright, strategic, capable, loyal, and articulate, which is w=
hy I chose him as my successor. He would make an outstanding treasury secre=
tary, if he is chosen.=E2=80=9D <br/></td>
